<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>出版物 |皮尤研究中心</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/publications/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Fri, 24 Apr 2026 12:56:04 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>美国人对特朗普在乌克兰问题上的决策越来越没有信心</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/global/2026/04/23/americans-have-become-less-confident-in-trumps-decision-making-on-ukraine/</link><description>共和党和民主党对乌克兰战争仍然有不同的看法，尽管他们对俄罗斯和普京的看法总体上是负面的。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 24 Apr 2026 01:25:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/global/2026/04/23/americans-have-become-less-confident-in-trumps-decision-making-on-ukraine/</guid></item><item><title>天主教在许多国家因宗教信仰的转变而失去了人们，而新教则在一些国家获得了胜利。</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/23/catholicism-has-lost-people-to-religious-switching-in-many-countries-while-protestantism-has-gained-in-some/</link><description>在基督教内部，宗教转变对天主教和新教这两个最大的群体产生了不同的影响。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 24 Apr 2026 01:10:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/23/catholicism-has-lost-people-to-religious-switching-in-many-countries-while-protestantism-has-gained-in-some/</guid></item><item><title>有关美国夏威夷原住民和太平洋岛民的主要事实</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/22/key-facts-about-native-hawaiians-and-pacific-islanders-in-the-u-s/</link><description>美国约有 170 万人是夏威夷原住民或太平洋岛民 (NHPI)，他们的根源可追溯到夏威夷、关岛、萨摩亚或大洋洲的其他太平洋岛屿。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 23 Apr 2026 01:26:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/22/key-facts-about-native-hawaiians-and-pacific-islanders-in-the-u-s/</guid></item><item><title>关于生活在混合家庭中的美国儿童的 5 个事实</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/21/5-facts-about-u-s-children-living-in-blended-families/</link><description>17% 的 18 岁以下美国儿童大部分时间或全部时间生活在混合家庭中，其中包括继父母、继兄弟姐妹或同父异母的兄弟姐妹。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 22 Apr 2026 01:20:46 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/21/5-facts-about-u-s-children-living-in-blended-families/</guid></item><item><title>美国人寻找或偶然发现什么类型的新闻？</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/20/what-types-of-news-do-americans-seek-out-or-happen-to-come-across/</link><description>大约一半的美国成年人 (49%) 表示，他们获取新闻主要是因为碰巧看到新闻，这一比例高于 2019 年的 39%。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 22 Apr 2026 01:05:46 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/20/what-types-of-news-do-americans-seek-out-or-happen-to-come-across/</guid></item><item><title>美国人更有可能说特朗普不太信教或根本不信教</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/16/americans-have-become-more-likely-to-say-trump-is-not-too-or-not-at-all-religious/</link><description>在特朗普最坚定的支持者中，相对较少的人表示他们认为他非常虔诚。只有 8% 的共和党人和 5% 的白人福音派人士认为情况确实如此。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 17 Apr 2026 01:22:34 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/16/americans-have-become-more-likely-to-say-trump-is-not-too-or-not-at-all-religious/</guid></item><item><title>美国人因对国家政治制度的悲观态度而在国际上脱颖而出</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/15/americans-stand-out-internationally-for-their-pessimism-about-the-nations-political-system/</link><description>高收入国家的人们通常不太可能说他们国家的政治制度需要重大改变或彻底改革。美国人是个例外。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 16 Apr 2026 01:25:09 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/15/americans-stand-out-internationally-for-their-pessimism-about-the-nations-political-system/</guid></item><item><title>青少年在 TikTok、Instagram 和 Snapchat 上的体验</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/internet/2026/04/15/teens-experiences-on-tiktok-instagram-and-snapchat/</link><description>青少年大多转向 TikTok、Instagram 和 Snapchat 寻找乐趣和联系。但关于消息传递、屏幕时间和网络欺凌的体验各不相同。以及青少年如何评价这些网站如何影响他们的心理健康。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 16 Apr 2026 01:10:09 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/internet/2026/04/15/teens-experiences-on-tiktok-instagram-and-snapchat/</guid></item><item><title>多项指标显示2025年美国民主健康状况下降</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/15/multiple-indicators-show-a-decline-in-the-health-of-americas-democracy-in-2025/</link><description>大多数美国人表示，美国的民主曾经是其他国家效仿的好榜样，但近年来却并非如此。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 16 Apr 2026 00:55:09 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/15/multiple-indicators-show-a-decline-in-the-health-of-americas-democracy-in-2025/</guid></item><item><title>近年来，美国人对中国的看法变得更加积极</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/14/americans-views-of-china-have-grown-somewhat-more-positive-in-recent-years/</link><description>大多数美国人仍然对中国持负面看法，但最近的一项调查显示，对中国的好感度有所上升，尤其是在民主党人和年轻人中。现在称中国为敌人的人越来越少了。由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 15 Apr 2026 01:19:33 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/14/americans-views-of-china-have-grown-somewhat-more-positive-in-recent-years/</guid></item></channel></rss>